abstract: Seven opposition candidates who took part in Cameroon's presidential election ask Supreme Court to call fresh vote within six months, warning that if their demand is not met, their supporters will take to streets in protest.
snippet: Seven opposition candidates who took part in the presidential election asked the Supreme Court on Monday to call a fresh vote within six months.
lead_paragraph: Seven opposition candidates who took part in the presidential election asked the Supreme Court on Monday to call a fresh vote within six months.

headline.main: Cameroon: Opposition Candidates Ask Supreme Court to Nullify Election
